            "id": 31,
            "type": "Basic page",
            "title": "Terms and Conditions",
            "created_at": "\u003Ctime datetime=\"2025-04-22T18:59:41+00:00\" class=\"datetime\"\u003ETue, 04/22/2025 - 18:59\u003C/time\u003E\n",
            "updated_at": "\u003Ctime datetime=\"2025-09-17T12:05:56+00:00\" class=\"datetime\"\u003EWed, 09/17/2025 - 12:05\u003C/time\u003E\n",
            "body": "\u003Cp\u003EBy using the Rerai Umntwana application (“Rerai Umntwana”) you accept these terms. If you do not agree with these terms, you must not use Rerai Umntwana.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContent\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERerai Umntwana is an app providing information and guidance to parents of young children (0-6 years old), on different aspects of child health, growth and development.  Rerai Umntwana also makes available a ledger where vaccination dates and health check-ups can be stored, and allows for users to set up notifications to remind them of these.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPlease do not use Rerai Umntwana for any medical purposes. The content of this app is not a substitute for health check-ups, medical examinations, assessments or diagnostic procedures. If you are concerned for your child’s health or development, UNICEF recommends that you consult your doctor or nurse. If the use of any information contained in the app leads to or causes loss or damage, UNICEF is not and cannot be responsible.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAll information and guidance in this app serve solely for, and are intended as, informational and educational purposes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAll the content provided in Rerai Umntwana is not for commercial use, and shall only be used for personal, domestic and private use. Its commercial use is prohibited. UNICEF shall have no liability for any loss of profit, loss of business, business interruption, or loss of business opportunity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EData and usage\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERerai Umntwana provides general informational content about children’s growth and development. It stores locally the data that is entered by users related to their children’s health and development. For information about the data that UNICEF collects and uses please see the Privacy Policy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERerai Umntwana may be able to provide notification for vaccination and health check up dates. These notifications are based on the processing of the information provided by the user and applying simple mathematical/statistical formulas. It is recommended that the user keeps a separate track of these dates and reminders, and does not only rely on Rerai Umntwana's notifications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContent updates\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough UNICEF makes reasonable efforts to update the information on Rerai Umntwana, UNICEF makes no representations, warranties or guarantees, whether express or implied, that the content on Rerai Umntwana is accurate, complete or up to date.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChanges to Terms and Conditions\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUNICEF might amend these terms from time to time. Every time you wish to use Rerai Umntwana, please check these terms to ensure you understand the terms that apply at that time.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChanges to the app\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUNICEF may update and change Rerai Umntwana from time to time to provide updated information, links or provide new functionality and reflect changes to our users' needs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuspension or withdrawal of the app\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERerai Umntwana is available free of charge. UNICEF does not guarantee that Rerai Umntwana, or any content on it, will always be available or be uninterrupted. UNICEF may suspend or withdraw or restrict the availability of all or any part of Rerai Umntwana for operational or other reason. UNICEF will try to give you reasonable notice of any suspension or withdrawal. UNICEF shall not have any liability for this. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaking other users aware of these Terms and Conditions\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf anyone else uses Rerai Umntwana through your device, you are also responsible for ensuring that they are aware of these terms of use and other applicable terms and conditions, and that they comply with them.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExternal links and resources\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERerai Umntwana may link to other websites and resources that are not under UNICEF's or its partner’s control. The inclusion of such links does not imply an endorsement or approval by UNICEF of any website, product or service.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUNICEF does not assume any responsibility or liability in respect of such websites, including, for example, responsibility or liability for the accuracy or reliability of any information, data, opinions, advice or statements made on those web sites.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntellectual Property Rights\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESome of the content available at Rerai Umntwana is created or provided by us or our other licensors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERerai Umntwana authorises the user to access and use the content and resources as set forth in these Terms of Use. Subject to these Terms of Use, the user may use the resources in the ways in which users are permitted to use them, as described on this site.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe user may only access and use the content resources on Rerai Umntwana, and may not transfer the content or resources to another person or \"mirror\" the content or resources on any other server.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe user is not allowed to create digital copies of the content or modify it, and must not use any illustrations, photographs, video or audio sequences or any graphics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EExcept for user content, the content and resources and all other parts of Rerai Umntwana are the property of UNICEF and/or licensors and are protected by copyright, patent and/or other proprietary intellectual property rights under national and international law. UNICEF and/or our licensors reserve all rights to the resources and this site that are not expressly granted in these Terms of Use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou may not reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble or otherwise access the source code for any software that may be used to operate this site. You may not remove any copyright, license or other notices on any resources or otherwise on this site.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPersonal information\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUNICEF will only use the personal information as set out in Rerai Umntwana's Privacy Policy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUNICEF name and emblem\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe UNICEF name and emblem are the exclusive property of UNICEF. They are protected under international law. Unauthorized use is prohibited. They may not be copied or reproduced in any way without the prior written permission of UNICEF. If you have any questions about this please contact UNICEF.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrivileges and Immunities\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENothing in or relating to these Terms of Use, the Privacy Policy or Rerai Umntwana shall be deemed a waiver of any of the privileges and immunities of UNICEF under the Convention on the Privileges and Immunities of the United Nations.\u003C/p\u003E",
